

VxAlignedForm(1vtcl)                         VxAlignedForm(1vtcl)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       VxAlignedForm  widgetName dataList

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Creates  one  or  more vertically aligned widgets within a
       form, with right-justified labels.

   OOppttiioonnss
       Widget hierarchy of the form.  A list of lists, each  con-
       taining  a  label  and another list containing the desired
       widget call and any desired arguments.

NNoottiicceess
       Each Label and Widget are in their own form.  Their widget
       names may be retrieved as follows: VxGetVar $name "form$n"
       VxGetVar $name "widget$n" VxGetVar $name  "label$n"  Where
       $name  is the name returned by the VxAlignedForm call, and
       $n is the position of the widget.   The  first  widget  is
       number 1.

       For example: set app [VtOpen "VxAlignedForm"]

       set  dlog  [VtFormDialog  $app.Dialog  -title  "My Aligned
       form"]

       set form [VxAlignedForm $dlog.Align\
         { {"Name:"          {VtText  -columns  15  -value  "John
       Doe"}}
           {"Address:"      {VtText -value "123 Hickory Street"}}
           {"Phone  Number:"  {VtText  -value  "800-555-1212"}}}]
       VtShow   $dlog  VtMainLoop  Produces  a  form  like  this:
       +-------------------------------------+   |          Name:
       [John  Doe            ]  |  |      Address:   [123 Hickory
       Street  ]  |  |Phone  Number:   [800-555-1212        ]   |
       +-------------------------------------+

